{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"2936","heading":"Scientific assessment","label":"2936 Scientific assessment","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2936","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/ch56A/schI","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs2936","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2936/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2936","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs2936%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"integrates, evaluates, and interprets the findings of the Program and discusses the scientific uncertainties associated with such findings;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2936/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2936","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs2936%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"analyzes the effects of global change on the natural environment, agriculture, energy production and use, land and water resources, transportation, human health and welfare, human social systems, and biological diversity; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2936/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2936","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs2936%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"analyzes current trends in global change, both human-inducted and natural, and projects major trends for the subsequent 25 to 100 years.1So in original. Probably should be “human-induced”.1","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
